help: Replace with `numpy.permute_dims`
1 | def func():
2 |     import numpy as np
3 | 
  -     np.transpose(np.array([[0, 1], [2, 3]]), (1, 0))
4 +     np.permute_dims(np.array([[0, 1], [2, 3]]), (1, 0))
5 | 
6 |     np.array([[0, 1], [2, 3]]).T

NPY202 `T` is not compatible with the Array API. For (stacked) matrix transpose use `.mT` instead. For any other permutation of axes use `np.permute_dims(...)`
